name: "Boyd Brain" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Felt pen, paint pen, and Sharpie on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and minor color correction...] Edgar had a lot to think about...so much that his bird-brain got a bit over-taxed and had to jump out of his skull and have a bit of a walk-about... Edgar makes a lot of mistakes. (Maybe he needed to hire a second bird for tougher contemplations... Perhaps...)  ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
